[{'comment_id': 1267381301, 'comment_body': '```suggestion
                "text": "HTML & PDF reports provide detailed insight of the known vulnerabilities (CVEs) found.  The generated Software Bill of Materials (SBOM) file gives you a list of all the components found and scanned by cve-bin-tool.  This may not represent everything you know to to be in your software, only what we were able to identify.   These results get automatically updated each time the CVE Binary Tool GitHub Action runs. You can disable this by dismissing the alert, then you won't receive any further HTML/PDF/SBOM reports."
```

In a perfect world we'd follow up with a sentence encouraging people to file issues/make checkers for components that weren't found automatically , or explain how to add them to your SBOM.  I don't think we need that in this PR until we're actually past the beta stage, though.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 7, 18, 23, 19, 24, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'terriko', 'type': 'User'}, {'comment_id': 1267384720, 'comment_body': 'Just noting that these will likely have to be regenerated if you add the extended text I suggested above.', 'comment_created': datetime.datetime(2023, 7, 18, 23, 24, 25, tzinfo=datetime.timezone.utc), 'commenter': 'terriko', 'type': 'User'}]
